<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870105-0041 </DOCNO><HL> REVIEW andamp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:Your Dance, Mr. Madison</HL><DD> 01/05/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><TEXT>   Curmudgeons are horrified by Warren Burger's plans for celebrating the bicentennial of the Constitution. He wants 50 million copies of the holy document printed on cereal boxes and sold in supermarket checkout lines. We're all for this, since it would increase the chances that some activist judges we know will finally see a copy. The Ballet Theatre of Annapolis, Md., is planning a ballet celebrating the ratification. In the spirit of original intent, we hope it will be set to 18th-century music. </TEXT></DOC>